<br>
You really should make a point of knowing the rules before you go. Don't assume that because the leader doesnt post that he is leading the raid primarily to get his own epic bit that he is leading the raid for the fun and a fair shot at loot.<br>
<br>
Leading a pickup raid can be alot of stress. They don't know until the last minute whether they will have the right people to do the raid, then they have to organize a bunch of individuals into a cohesive team. <br>
<br>
If it wasn't a pick up raid but, was as mentioned above, another guilds raid with invites, you shouldnt even expect to be offered the fiery vambraces that drop.<br>
<br>
Coming to R&amp;F to bitch about pick up raids...sheesh...may as well bitch about trains in KC or people requesting need before greed in OS.<br>
<br>
If you need something, take the initiative and organize the people to get it. You can't rely on getting what you need as a tagalong. Put yourself in the position to make the rules.<br>
